              <div class="Grid-cell">
                <div class="ProfileSidebar ProfileSidebar--withLeftAlignment">
  <div class="ProfileHeaderCard">
  <h1 class="ProfileHeaderCard-name">
    <a href="/Greg4Broxtowe" class="ProfileHeaderCard-nameLink u-textInheritColor js-nav">Greg Marshall</a>
  </h1>

  <h2 class="ProfileHeaderCard-screenname u-inlineBlock u-dir" dir="ltr">
    <a class="ProfileHeaderCard-screennameLink u-linkComplex js-nav" href="/Greg4Broxtowe">
      <span class="username u-dir" dir="ltr">@<b class="u-linkComplex-target">Greg4Broxtowe</b></span>
    </a>
  </h2>

  

      <p class="ProfileHeaderCard-bio u-dir" dir="ltr">Dad, Borough Councillor, Broxtowe born and bred. Labour parliamentary candidate for Broxtowe. <a href="/hashtag/FromBroxtoweForBroxtowe?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>FromBroxtoweForBroxtowe</b></a></p>

      <div class="ProfileHeaderCard-location ">
        <span class="Icon Icon--geo Icon--medium" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation"></span>
        <span class="ProfileHeaderCard-locationText u-dir" dir="ltr">
              Beeston, England

        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="ProfileHeaderCard-url ">
        <span class="Icon Icon--url Icon--medium" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation"></span>
        <span class="ProfileHeaderCard-urlText u-dir">  <a class="u-textUserColor" target="_blank" rel="me nofollow noopener" href="https://t.co/UBcYOq667f" title="http://www.broxtowelabour.com/">
    broxtowelabour.com
  </a>

</span>
      </div>


      <div class="ProfileHeaderCard-joinDate">
        <span class="Icon Icon--calendar Icon--medium" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation"></span>
        <span class="ProfileHeaderCard-joinDateText js-tooltip u-dir" dir="ltr" title="8:48 am - 1 May 2017">Joined May 2017</span>
      </div>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">A warm welcome awaits <a href="/RMTunion" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="26020906"><s>@</s><b>RMTunion</b></a> members if they decide to reaffiliate to the Labour Party.
Derby elected England's first Labour MP in 1900 and he was sponsored by the rail union.
Having the RMT back will help us elect a socialist Corbyn-led Labour Govt!<a href="https://t.co/8D1JniZpfr" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/stand-shoulder-to-shoulder-with-corbyn-rmt-activists-urge-members" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/stand-shoulder-to-shoulder-with-corbyn-rmt-activists-urge-members"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">morningstaronline.co.uk/article/stand-</span><span class="invisible">shoulder-to-shoulder-with-corbyn-rmt-activists-urge-members</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

  <ul>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">So the Tories <a href="/NottsCC" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="20507792"><s>@</s><b>NottsCC</b></a>. Have decided to take 1m out of Children's Centres over the next 2 years, shift the provision to church halls &amp; community centres and are asking for volunteers to run them. Children and families are the ones to suffer under the Tories.</p>

Parents very concerned but supportive of the campaign. Frankly it couldve been any school in <a href="/hashtag/Broxtowe?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Broxtowe</b></a> or <a href="/hashtag/Notts?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Notts</b></a> - vast majority are losing out and that means increased class sizes, less TAs and less resources for our kids <a href="/hashtag/endausterity?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>endausterity</b></a><a href="https://t.co/WuOMxXWcjF" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/broxtowelabour/status/976726272675020800" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/broxtowelabour/status/976726272675020800"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/broxtowelabour</span><span class="invisible">/status/976726272675020800</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Today I am supporting the <a href="/hashtag/FamiliesTogether?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>FamiliesTogether</b></a> Bill to change the unfair Home Office rules which prevent refugee children bringing their close family members to join them in the same way an adult can.

Labour respects the right to a family life.<a href="https://t.co/Zh5BGQoOOL" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/Zh5BGQoOOL</a></p>

        <div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">I sent a letter to Anna Soubry today. Theres a vote on <a href="/hashtag/UniversalCredit?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>UniversalCredit</b></a> which could leave over a million children without access to free school meals (17,000 in Notts alone).
I said it cannot be right to take hot dinners away from the children of her constituents. <a href="/hashtag/ProtectFSM?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>ProtectFSM</b></a><a href="https://t.co/jOdiKbqj1r" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/jOdiKbqj1r</a></p>

Trade Union reps are our country at its best. Normal people standing up for the colleagues and making their workplace a better place. 

Im proud to represent them and our movement in Parliament.<a href="https://t.co/DsvLWYpVpv" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/the_tuc/status/962941160925945856" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/the_tuc/status/962941160925945856"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/the_tuc/status</span><span class="invisible">/962941160925945856</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

<div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">On World Human Rights Day let's hope the government listens to <a href="/Debbie_abrahams" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="225857392"><s>@</s><b>Debbie_abrahams</b></a> &amp; <a href="/UKLabour" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="14291684"><s>@</s><b>UKLabour</b></a>. Causing misery for thousands isn't standing up for human rights in my book. <a href="/hashtag/StandUp4HumanRights?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>StandUp4HumanRights</b></a> <a href="/hashtag/UniversalCredit?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>UniversalCredit</b></a><a href="https://t.co/GLt9L0sMUl" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/debbie_abrahams/status/939766647769796609" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/debbie_abrahams/status/939766647769796609"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/debbie_abraham</span><span class="invisible">s/status/939766647769796609</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

          <div class="QuoteTweet-text tweet-text u-dir" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="2" dir="ltr">Today marks <span class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="201221959"><s>@</s><b>UKDHM</b></span> month.   <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Join me, James and rest of the fantastic <a href="/hashtag/TeamBroxtoweLabour?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>TeamBroxtoweLabour</b></a> out on the <a href="/hashtag/LabourDoorstep?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>LabourDoorstep</b></a> in <a href="/hashtag/Stapleford?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Stapleford</b></a> &amp; <a href="/hashtag/Chilwell?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Chilwell</b></a> this Saturday <a href="/hashtag/NG9?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>NG9</b></a> <a href="/hashtag/BetterOffWithLabour?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>BetterOffWithLabour</b></a> <a href="/hashtag/ForTheMany?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>ForTheMany</b></a><a href="https://t.co/vmNdAwpcuh" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/jameswjacobs/status/932638950870736896" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/jameswjacobs/status/932638950870736896"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/jameswjacobs/s</span><span class="invisible">tatus/932638950870736896</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

        <div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Our <a href="/hashtag/teambroxtowelabour?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>teambroxtowelabour</b></a> folk are having a great evening out watching and singing along with <a href="/billybragg" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="13496142"><s>@</s><b>billybragg</b></a> in <a href="/hashtag/Nottingham?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Nottingham</b></a>, celebrating <a href="/Greg4Broxtowe" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="859072140024442881"><s>@</s><b>Greg4Broxtowe</b></a> getting selected to become Broxtowe's next Labour MP.           <p class="u-hiddenVisually" aria-hidden="true" data-aria-label-part="1">Greg Marshall Retweeted The Labour Party</p>


<div class="js-tweet-text-container">
  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">It's a great honour to be selected for <a href="/UKLabour" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="14291684"><s>@</s><b>UKLabour</b></a> here in my home of <a href="/hashtag/Broxtowe?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Broxtowe</b></a>! HUGE thank you to <a href="/broxtowelabour" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="136990206"><s>@</s><b>broxtowelabour</b></a> members, to the other candidates and to all those who lent their support. My campaign starts here - for <a href="/hashtag/Broxtowe?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Broxtowe</b></a>, for <a href="/hashtag/Labour?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>Labour</b></a> and <a href="/hashtag/ForTheMany?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>ForTheMany</b></a> <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/270a.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Raised fist" aria-label="Emoji: Raised fist" /><a href="https://t.co/MUsNfzFYJN" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/UKLabour/status/931883010500300801" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/UKLabour/status/931883010500300801"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/UKLabour/statu</span><span class="invisible">s/931883010500300801</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>
</div>


<p class="u-hiddenVisually" aria-hidden="true" data-aria-label-part="3">Greg Marshall added,</p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">Myself and over 130 <a href="/UKLabour" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="14291684"><s>@</s><b>UKLabour</b></a> MPs have written to <a href="/BootsUK" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="545087869"><s>@</s><b>BootsUK</b></a> re the failure to roll out their cheaper emergency contraception by October, as promised earlier in the year. This must be addressed quickly as we enter the festive period!<a href="https://t.co/QEphEYWagg" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" data-pre-embedded="true" dir="ltr">pic.twitter.com/QEphEYWagg</a></p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">If you are a student at <a href="/TrentUni" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="29196791"><s>@</s><b>TrentUni</b></a> I will be taking part in @NTUPoliticsIR <a href="/hashtag/GE2017?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>GE2017</b></a> debate at <a href="/Trentstudents" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="45827920"><s>@</s><b>Trentstudents</b></a> NTSU this afternoon <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f44d.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="Thumbs up sign" aria-label="Emoji: Thumbs up sign" /><a href="https://t.co/8oo8yllk3n" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/NTUPoliticsIR/status/867692610655277056" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/NTUPoliticsIR/status/867692610655277056"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/NTUPoliticsIR/</span><span class="invisible">status/867692610655277056</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>

      <li class="embed-link js-actionEmbedTweet" data-nav="embed_tweet">
        <button type="button" class="dropdown-link">Embed Tweet</button>
      </li>
  </ul>
</div>

</div>

  </div>

      </div>

        <button type="button" class="dropdown-link">Copy link to Tweet</button>

          <div class="QuoteTweet-text tweet-text u-dir" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="2" dir="ltr">See <span rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="http://nickpalmer.org.uk" class="twitter-timeline-link" target="_blank" title="http://nickpalmer.org.uk"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">http://</span><span class="js-display-url">nickpalmer.org.uk</span><span class="invisible"></span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></span> for why I'm backing Greg Marshall to take on Anna Soubry - follow him on <span class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="859072140024442881"><s>@</s><b>greg4broxtowe</b></span>  to see him campaign.</div>
